# Code owners for the ari-skills registry.
#
# Referenced by GOVERNANCE.md as the canonical list of maintainers. Ownership
# here is about *review responsibility*, not permissions — the actual merge
# rights live in the repo's collaborator settings.
#
# This file only has teeth when branch protection has "Require review from
# Code Owners" enabled. See GOVERNANCE.md → Branch protection rules.

# Default owner for everything not matched below.
* @keithvassallomt

# ── High-trust paths ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Everything below is load-bearing for the trust chain. GOVERNANCE.md asks
# for extra scrutiny on these, and for a second reviewer once there is more
# than one maintainer.

# Workflows are the trust anchor: they hold the signing key. A typo here can
# leak it. Always review the diff line by line.
/.github/                   @keithvassallomt

# The generated catalogue every client reads to decide what to install and
# whether a bundle's hash is right. CI owns it — a hand-edit here is either a
# mistake or an attack.
/index.json                 @keithvassallomt

# Signed release artifacts and their signatures. Also CI-generated.
/bundles/                   @keithvassallomt
/manifests/                 @keithvassallomt

# The validator and sideload tooling every contributor runs locally.
/tools/                     @keithvassallomt

# The SDK every WASM skill compiles against.
/sdk/                       @keithvassallomt

# The rules themselves.
/GOVERNANCE.md              @keithvassallomt
/SECURITY.md                @keithvassallomt
/.github/CODEOWNERS         @keithvassallomt
